The paper discusses techniques for scaling up recursive query processing, which is a common problem in database systems (cs.DB). The paper also mentions parallel processing and performance optimization, which are topics in distributed computing (cs.DC) and algorithms and data structures (cs.DS). The use of Datalog, a logic programming language, suggests that the paper may also be relevant to programming languages (cs.PL). Finally, the paper discusses the application of these techniques to various domains, including program analysis and decision making, which fall under software engineering (cs.SE).
